     <div id="unit-head">
      <h1>
       <a href="http://policy.uncg.edu">
        Policies at UNCG
       </a>
      </h1>
     </div>
     <div class="content-page-sidebar" id="content">
      <div class="bottom-border" style="height:180px; ">
       <div id="whatsNew">
        <h2>
         What's New
        </h2>
        <p>
         Revised -
         <a href="/university-policies/consortium/">
          Greater Greensboro Consortium Cross Registration Agreement
         </a>
        </p>
       </div>
       <p>
        This page is a landing site for many UNCG policies. Please note that this site is under development and not all University policies are linked here. However, we have provided ways for you to access information quickly, including providing a link to the searchable University Policy Manual. If you have questions about or suggestions for this page or to submit a policy for review, please contact the Policy Advisory Group at
        <a href="mailto:policy@uncg.edu.">
         policy@uncg.edu
        </a>
        .
       </p>
      </div>
      <br class="clear"/>
      <div class="column">
       <div class="category categoryTop">
        <a href="/university-policies/">
         <img alt="University Policy Manual" src="images/minerva2.jpg"/>
        </a>
        <h2>
         <a href="/university-policies/">
          University Policy Manual
         </a>
        </h2>
        <p>
         Searchable manual of Chancellor-approved and Board of Trustees-approved policies with broad impact.
        </p>
       </div>
       <div class="category">
        <a href="http://www.uncg.edu/baf/polproc.html">
         <img alt="Faculty Policies" src="images/faculty.jpg"/>
        </a>
        <h2>
         <a href="https://provost.uncg.edu/policies-procedures-forms/">
          Academic Affairs
         </a>
        </h2>
        <p>
         Polices that cover academic freedom, tenure, and related faculty personnel topics.
        </p>
       </div>
       <div class="category">
        <a href="research.html">
         <img alt="Research" src="images/research2.jpg"/>
        </a>
        <h2>
         <a href="research.html">
          Research
         </a>
        </h2>
        <p>
         Policies that cover research and research topics for researchers and support staff.
        </p>
       </div>
       <div class="category">
        <a href="https://hrs.uncg.edu/Policies/">
         <img alt="Human Resources" src="images/hr-small2.jpg"/>
        </a>
        <h2>
         <a href="https://hrs.uncg.edu/Policies/">
          Human Resources
         </a>
        </h2>
        <p>
         Policies and information impacting employee groups and their working relationships within the University.
        </p>
       </div>
      </div>
      <div class="column columnRight">
       <div class="category categoryTop">
        <h2>
         <a href="safety.html">
          <img alt="Public Safety and Health" height="80" src="images/campus-safety2.jpg" width="120"/>
         </a>
         <a href="safety.html">
          Public Safety &amp; Risk Management
         </a>
        </h2>
        <p>
         Policies generally related to campus security, emergency planning, and emergency response.
        </p>
       </div>
       <div class="category">
        <a href="student.html">
         <img alt="Students" src="images/student2b.jpg"/>
        </a>
        <h2>
         <a href="student.html">
          Student Affairs
         </a>
        </h2>
        <p>
         Policies that cover the co-curricular, residential, and academic functions of student life.
        </p>
       </div>
       <div class="category">
        <a href="http://www.uncg.edu/baf/polproc.html">
         <img alt="Business Affairs" src="images/business-small2.jpg"/>
        </a>
        <h2>
         <a href="https://baf.uncg.edu/policies-procedures/">
          Business Affairs
         </a>
        </h2>
        <p>
         Policies generally related to accounting, budgeting, procurement, travel and other financial functions.
        </p>
       </div>
       <div class="category">
        <a href="http://its.uncg.edu/Technology_Policies/">
         <img alt="Information Technology" src="images/computing2.jpg"/>
        </a>
        <h2>
         <a href="http://its.uncg.edu/Technology_Policies/">
          Information Technology
         </a>
        </h2>
        <p>
         Policies that cover systems, access, data and related issues.
        </p>
       </div>
      </div>
     </div>
     <div id="three-col-sidebar">
      <h2 class="right-col-heading">
       What are University Policies?
      </h2>
      <p>
       University policies are rules that enhance organizational agility, minimize risk, and set behavioral expectations.
      </p>
      <h2 class="right-col-heading">
       What is the Policy Advisory Group (PAG)?
      </h2>
      <p>
       PAG is a standing committee of university faculty and staff (including University Counsel/designee), appointed by the Chancellor/designee, who reviews full drafts of all proposed, new and substantively revised University policies.
      </p>
